{
  "id": "feature-perf-014-polling-to-push",
  "title": "Replace Polling Intervals with WebSocket Push Updates",
  "category": "Performance",
  "description": "## Problem\nMultiple UI components use polling intervals (3-60 seconds) to check for data changes, even though the server already has WebSocket infrastructure for push updates. This creates unnecessary HTTP requests, increases server load, and introduces delays in data freshness (users wait up to the polling interval to see changes).\n\n## Current Polling Patterns\n\n| Component | File | Interval | What It Polls | HTTP Requests/Min |\n|-----------|------|----------|---------------|-------------------|\n| Running Agents | `use-running-agents.ts:9,12` | 15s (or 10s during title gen) | ALL features from ALL projects | 4-6/min per project |\n| Usage Tracking | `use-usage-tracking.ts:27` | 45s | Claude/Codex API usage | ~1.3/min |\n| Remote Sync | `use-remote-sync.ts:26-28` | 60s (default), min 10s | Git remote status | 1-6/min |\n| Session Status | `session-manager.tsx:101-113` | 3s | Running state for each session | 20/min per session |\n| Agent Info Panel | `agent-info-panel.tsx:226` | 3s | Agent output for in-progress features | 20/min per feature |\n| Board Auto-Mode | `board-view.tsx:1503` | 3s | Auto-mode feature state | 20/min |\n\n### Worst Case: With 3 projects, 5 sessions, 3 features running:\n~100+ HTTP requests per minute just from polling.\n\n## Most Impactful - Running Agents Hook (`use-running-agents.ts`):\n```typescript\n// Lines 117-134: Fetches ALL features from ALL projects every 15 seconds\nconst featuresPromises = currentProjects.map(async (project) => {\n  try {\n    const result = await featuresApi.getAll(project.path);  // Full feature load per project!\n    if (result.success && result.features) {\n      return result.features.filter(f => f.status === 'in_progress' || f.status === 'running');\n    }\n  }\n});\n```\n\n## Session Manager Polling (`session-manager.tsx:101-113`):\n```typescript\nuseEffect(() => {\n  if (runningSessions.size === 0 && !isCurrentSessionThinking) return;\n  const interval = setInterval(async () => {\n    if (sessions.length > 0) {\n      await checkRunningSessions(sessions);  // HTTP request for EACH session\n    }\n  }, 3000);\n  return () => clearInterval(interval);\n}, [sessions, runningSessions.size, isCurrentSessionThinking]);\n```\n\n## Required Changes\n\n### 1. Create Server-Side Push Events for Frequently-Polled Data\nAdd new WebSocket event types:\n- `feature_status_changed` - emitted when any feature's status changes (already partially exists)\n- `agent_session_state_changed` - emitted when agent session starts/stops\n- `usage_updated` - emitted after API calls with updated usage counters\n- `remote_sync_update` - emitted after git remote checks complete\n\n### 2. Replace Running Agents Polling\n- Subscribe to `feature_status_changed` events\n- Maintain running agent count in Zustand store, updated by event handler\n- Remove the 15s polling interval entirely\n- Keep a single initial fetch on mount, then rely on events\n\n### 3. Replace Session Manager Polling\n- Subscribe to `agent:stream` events which already include `sessionId`\n- Track running sessions from these events instead of polling\n- Remove the 3s polling interval\n\n### 4. Replace Agent Info Panel Polling\n- Subscribe to auto-mode events for the specific feature being viewed\n- Events already stream agent output - use them directly\n- Remove the 3s polling interval\n\n### 5. Keep Polling as Fallback Only\n- Increase polling intervals to 60-120s as a \"catch-up\" mechanism\n- Primary updates come from WebSocket events\n- Polling only serves as a safety net for missed events or reconnection\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n### Server:\n- `apps/server/src/lib/events.ts` - Add new event types\n- `apps/server/src/services/agent-service.ts` - Emit session state change events\n- `apps/server/src/services/claude-usage-service.ts` - Emit usage update events\n- `libs/types/src/event.ts` - Add new event type definitions\n\n### Client:\n- `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-running-agents.ts` - Replace polling with event subscription\n- `apps/ui/src/components/session-manager.tsx` - Replace polling with event subscription\n- `apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/components/kanban-card/agent-info-panel.tsx` - Replace polling\n- `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-usage-tracking.ts` - Replace polling with event + longer fallback interval\n- `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-remote-sync.ts` - Add event-based updates with long fallback polling\n\n## Expected Impact\n- 80-90% reduction in HTTP polling requests\n- Real-time data freshness (instant updates instead of 3-15s delay)\n- Reduced server CPU load (fewer request handling, fewer disk reads)\n- Lower network bandwidth usage\n- Better battery life on laptops (fewer network wakeups)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- Running agents indicator updates instantly when features start/stop (not 15s delay)\n- Session running state updates instantly via WebSocket\n- Network tab shows dramatically fewer polling requests\n- UI still works correctly if WebSocket briefly disconnects (fallback polling kicks in)\n- No data staleness issues - events reliably update all displayed data\n- Page refresh still works (initial fetch on mount, then events)\n\n## Reference\n- `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-auto-mode.ts` - Good example of event-driven updates via WebSocket\n- `apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/hooks/use-board-features.ts` - Existing event subscription pattern",
