    "content": "I'll analyze the codebase to understand the existing patterns before generating the specification.\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T20:47:41.925Z] 🔧 Tool: Task\nInput: {\n  \"description\": \"Explore event system and WebSocket\",\n  \"prompt\": \"I need to understand the existing WebSocket event system in this codebase. Please read and summarize the key parts of these files:\\n\\n1. `apps/server/src/lib/events.ts` - The event emitter system\\n2. `libs/types/src/event.ts` - Event type definitions\\n3. `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-auto-mode.ts` - Example of event-driven updates (referenced as good pattern)\\n4. `apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/hooks/use-board-features.ts` - Existing event subscription pattern\\n\\nFor each file, tell me:\\n- What event types exist\\n- How events are emitted on the server\\n- How events are subscribed to on the client\\n- The WebSocket message format/protocol\\n- Any existing patterns for push-based updates\\n\\nBe thorough - read the full files.\",\n  \"subagent_type\": \"Explore\",\n  \"run_in_background\": true\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T20:47:56.939Z] 🔧 Tool: Task\nInput: {\n  \"description\": \"Explore polling hooks and components\",\n  \"prompt\": \"I need to understand the current polling patterns in these files. Please read each file fully and summarize:\\n\\n1. `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-running-agents.ts` - Running agents polling\\n2. `apps/ui/src/components/session-manager.tsx` - Session manager polling  \\n3. `apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/components/kanban-card/agent-info-panel.tsx` - Agent info panel polling\\n4. `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-usage-tracking.ts` - Usage tracking polling\\n5. `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-remote-sync.ts` - Remote sync polling\\n6. `apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view.tsx` - Board auto-mode polling (look around line 1503)\\n\\nFor each file tell me:\\n- Exactly what data is being polled and how (API calls, endpoints)\\n- The polling interval\\n- What triggers polling start/stop\\n- What state is updated from the polling\\n- How the data is consumed by the UI\\n- Any conditions that change polling behavior\\n\\nBe thorough and precise with line numbers.\",\n  \"subagent_type\": \"Explore\",\n  \"run_in_background\": true\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T20:48:00.766Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DYLANS~1\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\Temp\\\\claude\\\\C--Users-DylanSmart-Downloads-automaker-pr\\\\tasks\\\\ac4592b.output\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T20:48:21.950Z] 🔧 Tool: TaskOutput\nInput: {\n  \"task_id\": \"ac4592b\",\n  \"block\": true,\n  \"timeout\": 30000\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T20:48:22.097Z] 🔧 Tool: TaskOutput\nInput: {\n  \"task_id\": \"ac90b94\",\n  \"block\": true,\n  \"timeout\": 30000\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T20:48:56.130Z] 🔧 Tool: TaskOutput\nInput: {\n  \"task_id\": \"ac90b94\",\n  \"block\": true,\n  \"timeout\": 60000\n}\nNow let me also explore the server-side services that need to emit new events:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T20:49:30.290Z] 🔧 Tool: Task\nInput: {\n  \"description\": \"Explore server services for events\",\n  \"prompt\": \"I need to understand the server-side services that currently emit events or would need to emit new events. Please read these files and summarize:\\n\\n1. `apps/server/src/services/agent-service.ts` - Focus on: how agent sessions are started/stopped, where events are emitted, what state transitions happen\\n2. `apps/server/src/services/claude-usage-service.ts` - How usage data is tracked and returned\\n3. `apps/server/src/services/auto-mode-service.ts` - How auto-mode emits events (this is already event-driven)\\n4. `apps/server/src/index.ts` - How the WebSocket server is set up and how events flow from emitter to WebSocket clients\\n\\nFor each file, focus on:\\n- Where events are currently emitted\\n- What event types are used\\n- Where new events could be naturally added\\n- The WebSocket broadcasting mechanism\\n\\nBe thorough with exact line numbers.\",\n  \"subagent_type\": \"Explore\",\n  \"run_in_background\": true\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T20:49:44.335Z] 🔧 Tool: Task\nInput: {\n  \"description\": \"Explore WebSocket client infrastructure\",\n  \"prompt\": \"I need to understand how the UI connects to the server WebSocket and receives events. Please explore:\\n\\n1. `apps/ui/src/lib/http-api-client.ts` - The API client, especially WebSocket connection setup\\n2. `apps/ui/src/lib/electron.ts` - The electron API bridge, especially event listeners\\n3. `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-init-script-events.ts` - How script events are initialized\\n4. `apps/ui/src/store/app-store.ts` - The Zustand store, especially any WebSocket-related state\\n5. `apps/ui/src/preload.ts` - The Electron preload script to understand the IPC bridge\\n\\nFor each file, focus on:\\n- How WebSocket events are received in the browser/electron\\n- How events flow from WebSocket to React components\\n- The available event subscription APIs that hooks can use\\n- Any existing patterns for subscribing to server-push events\\n\\nBe thorough with exact line numbers.\",\n  \"subagent_type\": \"Explore\",\n  \"run_in_background\": true\n}\n\n\nLet me retrieve the results from both background agents:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T20:50:00.449Z] 🔧 Tool: TaskOutput\nInput: {\n  \"task_id\": \"a886891\",\n  \"block\": true,\n  \"timeout\": 30000\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T20:50:03.361Z] 🔧 Tool: TaskOutput\nInput: {\n  \"task_id\": \"a503102\",\n  \"block\": true,\n  \"timeout\": 60000\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T20:51:10.549Z] 🔧 Tool: TaskOutput\nInput: {\n  \"task_id\": \"a886891\",\n  \"block\": true,\n  \"timeout\": 60000\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T20:51:10.729Z] 🔧 Tool: TaskOutput\nInput: {\n  \"task_id\": \"a503102\",\n  \"block\": true,\n  \"timeout\": 60000\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T20:52:17.682Z] 🔧 Tool: TaskOutput\nInput: {\n  \"task_id\": \"a503102\",\n  \"block\": true,\n  \"timeout\": 120000\n}\nNow I have a thorough understanding of the entire event system. Let me also quickly check the Electron API type definitions to understand how event subscription methods are typed:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T20:52:50.212Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\lib\\\\electron.ts\",\n  \"offset\": 1,\n  \"limit\": 100\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-12T20:52:50.771Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\libs\\\\types\\\\src\\\\event.ts\"\n}\nNow I have a complete understanding of the architecture. Let me generate the full specification.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Problem Statement\n\nMultiple UI components poll the server at intervals of 3-60 seconds to check for data changes, generating 100+ unnecessary HTTP requests per minute in worst-case scenarios. The server already has a mature WebSocket event infrastructure that broadcasts events to all connected clients. By leveraging this existing push infrastructure for frequently-polled data (running agents, session status, agent output, usage tracking), we can eliminate ~80-90% of polling requests while delivering instant data freshness.\n\n## 2. User Story\n\nAs a **developer using Automaker**, I want **the UI to update instantly when features start/stop, sessions change state, and usage data refreshes**, so that **I see real-time status without waiting 3-15 seconds for polling intervals, and my machine isn't wasting CPU/network on unnecessary HTTP requests**.\n\n## 3. Acceptance Criteria\n\n**Happy Path - Running Agents:**\n- GIVEN a feature starts executing in auto-mode, WHEN the server emits a `feature:status-changed` event, THEN the running agents indicator updates within 1 second (not 15s)\n- GIVEN the UI is open with multiple projects, WHEN features change status across projects, THEN the running agent count reflects all changes without polling all projects\n\n**Happy Path - Session Status:**\n- GIVEN an agent session starts processing, WHEN the server emits a session state event via `agent:stream`, THEN the session list shows the running indicator immediately (not after 3s polling)\n- GIVEN a session completes, WHEN the completion event arrives via WebSocket, THEN the spinning indicator stops immediately\n\n**Happy Path - Agent Info Panel:**\n- GIVEN a feature card is visible with an in-progress feature, WHEN auto-mode emits task progress events, THEN the panel updates task status in real-time without polling\n- GIVEN a feature card scrolls out of view, THEN no polling or event processing occurs for that card\n\n**Happy Path - Usage Tracking:**\n- GIVEN usage data changes after an API call, WHEN the server emits a `usage:updated` event, THEN the usage popover shows fresh data without waiting 45s\n\n**Edge Case - WebSocket Disconnection:**\n- GIVEN the WebSocket disconnects temporarily, WHEN the connection is lost, THEN fallback polling activates at a longer interval (60-120s) to catch up\n- GIVEN the WebSocket reconnects, WHEN the connection is restored, THEN an initial fetch occurs to sync state, and polling is disabled again\n\n**Edge Case - Page Refresh:**\n- GIVEN the user refreshes the page, WHEN the page loads, THEN an initial fetch on mount populates data, then events take over\n\n**Error Handling:**\n- GIVEN the server emits a malformed event, WHEN the client receives it, THEN parsing errors are caught and logged without crashing the UI\n\n## 4. Technical Context\n\n| Aspect | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Affected Files (Server) | `libs/types/src/event.ts`, `apps/server/src/services/agent-service.ts`, `apps/server/src/services/claude-usage-service.ts`, `apps/server/src/services/auto-mode-service.ts` |\n| Affected Files (Client) | `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-running-agents.ts`, `apps/ui/src/components/session-manager.tsx`, `apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/components/kanban-card/agent-info-panel.tsx`, `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-usage-tracking.ts`, `apps/ui/src/hooks/use-remote-sync.ts`, `apps/ui/src/lib/http-api-client.ts` |\n| Dependencies | None new - leverages existing WebSocket infrastructure |\n| Constraints | Must work in both Electron and web browser mode; events broadcast to all clients (no per-client filtering); `auto-mode:event` wrapper pattern must be followed for auto-mode events |\n| Patterns to Follow | `use-auto-mode.ts` event subscription via `api.autoMode.onEvent()`, `use-board-features.ts` reload-on-event pattern, `subscribeToEvent()` in `http-api-client.ts` |\n\n## 5. Non-Goals\n\n- **Remote sync push events**: Git remote sync (`use-remote-sync.ts`) checks external git remotes which the server doesn't monitor proactively. Converting this to push requires a server-side polling/watcher mechanism which is out of scope. We will only increase its fallback interval.\n- **Board auto-mode feature-start loop** (`board-view.tsx:1549`): This is a control loop that decides *when to start features*, not a data display poll. It reads local state and calls `handleStartImplementation()`. Converting it to event-driven would require a fundamentally different architecture. We leave it as-is.\n- **Per-client event filtering**: The WebSocket broadcasts all events to all clients. Adding per-client subscription filters is a larger infrastructure change.\n- **Typed event payloads**: All event payloads are currently `unknown`. Adding full type safety to payloads is a separate effort.\n\n## 6. Implementation Tasks\n\n```tasks\n## Phase 1: Server-Side Event Infrastructure\n- [ ] T001: Add new event types to EventType union (`feature:status-changed`, `session:state-changed`, `usage:updated`) | File: libs/types/src/event.ts\n- [ ] T002: Emit `feature:status-changed` events from auto-mode service when feature status transitions occur | File: apps/server/src/services/auto-mode-service.ts\n- [ ] T003: Emit `session:state-changed` events from agent service when sessions start/stop/complete | File: apps/server/src/services/agent-service.ts\n- [ ] T004: Add event emitter to usage service and emit `usage:updated` after fetching fresh usage data | File: apps/server/src/services/claude-usage-service.ts\n- [ ] T005: Wire usage service event emitter in server initialization | File: apps/server/src/index.ts\n\n## Phase 2: Client-Side Event Subscription Infrastructure\n- [ ] T006: Register new event types in HTTP API client's event type list and add subscription methods | File: apps/ui/src/lib/http-api-client.ts\n\n## Phase 3: Replace Running Agents Polling\n- [ ] T007: Replace 15s polling in use-running-agents with event subscription for `feature:status-changed` and `auto-mode:event`, keeping initial fetch on mount and 120s fallback polling | File: apps/ui/src/hooks/use-running-agents.ts\n\n## Phase 4: Replace Session Manager Polling\n- [ ] T008: Replace 3s polling in session-manager with `agent:stream` and `session:state-changed` event subscription, keeping initial fetch on mount and 60s fallback polling | File: apps/ui/src/components/session-manager.tsx\n\n## Phase 5: Replace Agent Info Panel Polling\n- [ ] T009: Replace 3s polling in agent-info-panel with `auto-mode:event` subscription for task progress, keeping IntersectionObserver gating and 60s fallback polling | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/components/kanban-card/agent-info-panel.tsx\n\n## Phase 6: Replace Usage Tracking Polling\n- [ ] T010: Replace 45s polling in use-usage-tracking with `usage:updated` event subscription, increasing fallback interval to 120s | File: apps/ui/src/hooks/use-usage-tracking.ts\n\n## Phase 7: Adjust Remote Sync Fallback\n- [ ] T011: Increase default polling interval in use-remote-sync from 30s to 60s (no push conversion - server doesn't monitor git remotes) | File: apps/ui/src/hooks/use-remote-sync.ts\n```\n\n## 7. Success Metrics\n\n- Running agents indicator updates within 1 second of feature status change (vs. 15s before)\n- Session running indicators update within 1 second (vs. 3s before)\n- Agent info panel task progress updates in real-time via events (vs. 3s polling)\n- Network tab shows <10 polling requests per minute in steady state (vs. 100+ before)\n- Page refresh correctly loads initial state then switches to event-driven updates\n- WebSocket disconnect triggers fallback polling; reconnect restores event-driven mode\n- No regressions in data accuracy - all displayed data matches server state\n\n## 8. Risks & Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Missed events during WebSocket disconnect | Fallback polling at 60-120s intervals acts as safety net; initial fetch on reconnect syncs state |\n| Event storms during high-concurrency auto-mode (many features) | Client-side debouncing (already used in board-features); event handlers update refs/state without triggering cascading re-renders |\n| Breaking existing auto-mode event consumers | New `feature:status-changed` events are additive; existing `auto-mode:event` types unchanged |\n| Usage service currently has no event emitter dependency | Wire it in `index.ts` initialization alongside other services; minimal change |\n| Stale data if events are lost silently | Fallback polling serves as reconciliation mechanism; `isStale` tracking already exists in usage hook |",
